# The Business Trip

Three blocks of tempo work at 85% FTP. Nothing flashy, just honest work that builds your aerobic engine. Stay seated, keep your form tight, and clock in the miles. Tempo is the bread and butter of endurance cycling.

- 10:00 45%
  - :30 Warm up nice and easy
  - 5:00 Gradually bring the legs online
  - 3:00 First tempo block starts in 2 minutes
  - :30 Find a cadence around 85-90rpm
- 10:00 85%
  - :10 First tempo block — find your rhythm
  - 3:00 Breathing should be noticeable but controlled
  - 4:00 Halfway — stay on top of the gear, don't let it push you around
  - 2:00 Last minute of this block, hold your form
- 5:00 50%
  - :10 Recovery — keep the legs moving
  - 3:00 Next block in 2 minutes
- 10:00 85%
  - :10 Block two — settle right back in
  - 5:00 Halfway — you know the drill by now
  - 3:00 Two minutes to go, maintain that power
- 5:00 50%
  - :10 Recovery — one more to go
  - 3:00 Final block in 2 minutes, make it the best one
- 10:00 85%
  - :10 Last block — make it count
  - 5:00 Halfway through the final effort
  - 3:00 Final two minutes — hold the line
  - 1:00 Last minute, don't fade now
- 10:00 40%
  - :10 Clock out! Great session
  - 5:00 Easy spinning to cool down
